to maintain u.s. pre-eminence in information technology. celis was born and raised in monterrey, mexico and holds an engineering degree from the monterrey institute of technology, as well as master's and ph.d. degrees in computer science from the university of waterloo in canada. he currently holds 15 u.s. patents. in addition to his professional accomplishments, dr. celis has served as a board member of the washington state hispanic chamber of commerce and in 2001 founded the washington chapter of the (PARTY NAME) national hispanic assembly and became its first chairman. from 2005-2007, he served as national chairman of the (PARTY NAME) national hispanic assembly.</p></span>



